	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=174116><span id=Scholar>Branaddar</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>440 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.36]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Okay, let's clear it up...<br><br>Focuses do NOT stack. They act just like items with &quot;Effect: Haste(Worn)&quot; do... the higher effect will be used in checks.<br><br>So if you have these godly gloves, and, say, an improved damage 4 item that only ups damage by 10%, it will ignore the 10% item and do 25% more damage when you cast Strike of Solusek.<br><br>The same is true of all spell haste, mana preservation, improved damage, extended enhancement/affliction/etc type effects.<br><br>And as a side-note... affliction efficiency, which lowers mana costs, does not stack with mana preservation, though AE does reduce mana costs more than MP does (for the &quot;affliction&quot; line of spells, namely dots, a lot of debuffs and slows)</p>&nbsp;<br><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br><a href=HTTP://magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=939819 target=akztarg><span style='color: red;'><b>Bransback</a> and Branaddar Balefire</b></span style='color: red;'><br>Monk and Wizard of <a href=HTTP://www.eternalsovereign.org target=akztarg><span style='color: blue;'>Eternal Soveriegn</span style='color: blue;'></a><br><span style='color: green;'>Tholuxe Paells</span style='color: green;'></td></tr>
